title: Ubisoft Delays Skull and Bones... Again - Kinda Funny Games Daily 09.28.22
description:
Skull and Bones has been delayed again, big changes are coming to Overwatch 2, and Cyberpunk has sold 20 million copies. Blessing and Janet tackle it all on today's Games Daily.

Time Stamps - 
00:00:00 - Start
00:09:00 - Housekeeping

A new Kinda Funny Xcast is up right now all about Grounded 1.0. Greg joins the crew to talk about their review impressions. That’s up now on Youtube.com/KindaFunnyGames and on podcast services around the globe.

After this, over on YouTube.com/KindaFunny we will be live recording our review of Andore Episode 4 with Tim, Barrett, Saige, and Carboni!

The Roper Report  -

00:10:39 - Ubisoft is delaying Skull and Bones
00:22:53 - Wild Hearts, EA's Monster Hunter Contender, Is Out in February
00:29:16 - Pokemon announced this little Wiglett motherfucker
00:34:12 - Ad
00:36:25 - It’ll Take New Players About 100 Matches To Unlock All Original Heroes in Overwatch 2
00:49:32 - Cyberpunk has sold over 20 million copies
00:53:47 - Dark Pictures: Man of Medan and Little Hope get free current-gen upgrades
00:59:08 - PS Plus games for October have been revealed
01:00:46 - Out today
01:01:56 - You‘re Wrong
Tomorrow’s Hosts: Bless & Tim
